original: Engblom, Victor Emanuel, fil. dr, rektor, Borås, f. 21/9/92 i Kvidinge, Krist. 1., av folksk :lär. Sven E. o. Johanna Jonasdotter. G. 21 m. Maja Smith. Barn: Sven f. 22, civ:ekonom, Jerker 26, fil. stud., Claes 29, Göran 30. — Stud:ex. i Lund 11, fil. kand. 14, fil. mag. 15, fil. lic. 32, fil. dr i Lund 38. Res. t. Tys’kl. 07, 09, 21 o. 39, Engl. 13, 25 o. 39. E. lär. i Klippan 18-20, ord. ämneslär. i Skänninge 21, adj. i Upps. 29, lektor v. norra latin i Sthlm 40, rektor v. Borås h. a. 1. sed. 40. Rektor v. Skänninge komm. mellansk. 20-30, v. Nässjö samrealsk. 32-40. Led. av kyrkofullm. o. stads-fullm. i Nässjö. Skr.: On the Origin and Early Development of the Auxi-liary Do (grad:avh. 38). RNO.
translated: Engblom, Victor Emanuel, Ph.D., principal, Borås, born on September 21, 1892 in Kvidinge, Kristianstad County, to primary school teacher Sven E. and Johanna Jonasdotter. Married to Maja Smith in 1921, they have four children: Sven, born in 1922 and a graduate in economics, Jerker, born in 1926 and a student in philosophy, Claes, born in 1929, and Göran, born in 1930. Victor passed his school leaving exam in Lund in 1911, received his Bachelor's degree in 1914, Master's degree in 1915, Licentiate degree in 1932, and Ph.D. in Lund in 1938. He traveled to Germany in 1907, 1909, 1921, and 1939, and to England in 1913, 1925 and 1939. He was a teacher in Klippan from 1918-1920, a subject teacher in Skänninge from 1921, an assistant in Uppsala in 1929, a lecturer in Latin at the northern Latin school in Stockholm in 1940, and principal of Borås high school since 1940. He was also a principal in Skänninge community school from 1920-1930 and in Nässjö secondary school from 1932-1940. He was a member of the church council and city council in Nässjö. His work On the Origin and Early Development of the Auxiliary Do (doctoral thesis, 1938) was recognized with the Royal Order of the North Star (RNO).
